<div id="banner">
	<h1>More Crazy Haxies</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>The crazy people over at unsanity have put together <a href="http://www.unsanity.com/haxies/">some more haxies for OS X</a> including <a href="http://www.unsanity.com/haxies/metallifizer/">metalifizer</a> which can add or remove the brushed metal look to all your programs, <a href="http://www.unsanity.com/haxies/fruitmenu/">a Jaguar-compatible FruitMenu</a>, and <a href="http://www.unsanity.com/haxies/cleardock/">ClearDock</a>, which lets you change the dock background or remove it.  They&#8217;ve also released <a href="http://www.unsanity.com/haxies/ape/">Application Enhancer</a>, the backend that powers all the haxies.</p>

<p class="posted">posted September 10, 2002 11:59 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000585" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

